WEBVTT

01:40.380 --> 01:48.740
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP06]

03:03.139 --> 03:05.060
I think we have to talk about

03:05.060 --> 03:06.139
the performance.

03:06.699 --> 03:07.859
Yeah, I think it's a good idea

03:07.859 --> 03:08.979
to talk about it.

03:09.180 --> 03:10.940
So what ideas have you got?

03:16.940 --> 03:17.460
[Honey?]

03:18.259 --> 03:19.380
[Are you... Are you home?]

03:24.539 --> 03:25.139
Ruan Yu?

03:25.380 --> 03:26.780
Yeah, yeah, I'm almost home.

03:27.419 --> 03:27.940
[Okay.]

03:30.100 --> 03:31.539
[You're picking me up at the crossroads?]

03:34.220 --> 03:34.780
[Alright.]

03:36.539 --> 03:37.780
[I'll be there in five minutes.]

03:40.100 --> 03:41.100
[Are you being followed?]

03:44.460 --> 03:45.100
Stay calm.

03:45.620 --> 03:47.019
Head to where there are people and lights.

03:47.819 --> 03:48.340
[Tell him]

03:48.340 --> 03:49.500
[I'm on my way to you right now.]

03:49.699 --> 03:51.019
I'm already heading your way.

03:53.900 --> 03:54.620
I'm almost there.

03:59.139 --> 03:59.739
Uh,

04:00.340 --> 04:01.259
it's okay now, Mr. Xu.

04:01.259 --> 04:02.139
I'm home.

04:03.060 --> 04:05.620
[I guess I just overreacted.]

04:08.699 --> 04:09.419
Glad you're safe.

04:10.139 --> 04:11.060
Get some rest.

04:11.819 --> 04:13.139
I'm already dealing with

04:13.780 --> 04:14.780
those posts online.

04:17.419 --> 04:17.979
Honey?

04:18.819 --> 04:19.819
Are you... Are you home?

04:21.060 --> 04:21.739
Well,

04:22.180 --> 04:23.060
I'm so sorry.

04:23.660 --> 04:24.260
I meant to

04:24.260 --> 04:25.580
call a friend just now,

04:26.260 --> 04:27.539
but I dialed your number by mistake.

04:42.499 --> 04:43.220
What's wrong?

04:44.059 --> 04:45.020
Mr. Xu,

04:45.739 --> 04:46.179
there's

04:46.900 --> 04:47.580
a black van

04:47.580 --> 04:49.460
parked downstairs.

04:50.179 --> 04:51.379
[It wasn't there]

04:51.379 --> 04:52.140
[when I just got here.]

04:52.900 --> 04:54.059
Can you make out the license plate?

04:56.179 --> 04:57.020
Not really,

04:57.220 --> 04:58.260
but it looks like

04:59.020 --> 05:00.460
the kind of van used for abductions.

05:06.419 --> 05:07.660
It's probably not

05:07.660 --> 05:08.939
what you're worried about.

05:09.220 --> 05:10.059
Even if it is,

05:10.059 --> 05:11.419
they won't just break in.

05:11.900 --> 05:13.539
I need you to do two things right now:

05:13.820 --> 05:14.299
First,

05:14.619 --> 05:15.419
send me your location

05:15.619 --> 05:17.020
and your property management

05:17.020 --> 05:18.179
or security office's number.

05:18.700 --> 05:20.419
Second, grab your phone

05:20.700 --> 05:21.539
and check the peephole.

05:22.739 --> 05:23.220
Okay.

05:33.460 --> 05:34.260
Done.

05:37.979 --> 05:38.700
Stay quiet first.

05:40.179 --> 05:41.700
[If you see someone suspicious]

05:41.859 --> 05:42.260
[and they]

05:42.260 --> 05:43.299
haven't made a move,

05:43.700 --> 05:44.820
don't lock the door yet.

05:45.660 --> 05:47.059
Step back away from the door,

05:47.419 --> 05:48.220
turn on speakerphone,

05:48.379 --> 05:49.419
and call my name loudly.

05:49.820 --> 05:50.979
Say you're doing laundry

05:51.379 --> 05:52.059
and tell me to get the door.

05:52.660 --> 05:53.260
Understand?

05:54.499 --> 05:55.020
Understood.

05:56.020 --> 05:57.100
If they don't leave

05:57.499 --> 05:58.660
after you do that,

05:59.379 --> 06:00.499
lock the door immediately

06:00.820 --> 06:01.900
and call the police.

06:13.979 --> 06:14.539
What's wrong?

06:18.340 --> 06:18.739
Hello?

06:24.900 --> 06:25.660
[Sorry,]

06:26.100 --> 06:28.179
[the number you've dialed is powered off.]

06:29.059 --> 06:30.539
Ruan Yu? You home?

06:48.379 --> 06:49.619
It's me, Li Shican.

06:52.700 --> 06:53.299
Shican?

06:53.580 --> 06:54.260
What are you doing here?

06:55.299 --> 06:56.220
Didn't we agree

06:56.379 --> 06:57.539
to meet at our usual spot?

06:58.979 --> 06:59.900
I thought you called me

06:59.900 --> 07:00.900
about your livestream?

07:01.820 --> 07:02.939
You watched my livestream?

07:04.780 --> 07:05.739
Mingying and I were bored

07:05.739 --> 07:06.379
at home the other day,

07:06.379 --> 07:07.460
so we caught your stream.

07:09.179 --> 07:10.580
You two really cared about me.

07:11.820 --> 07:13.340
Can I come in?

07:13.780 --> 07:14.820
I'm kind of worried...

07:15.299 --> 07:16.340
Yeah, of course, come in.

07:22.900 --> 07:23.460
Shican,

07:23.780 --> 07:25.020
I don't have men's slippers here.

07:25.260 --> 07:26.220
Just keep your shoes on.

07:31.499 --> 07:32.419
Still no boyfriend?

07:34.419 --> 07:35.460
You weren't this gossipy

07:35.460 --> 07:36.299
before you entered show business.

07:40.499 --> 07:40.979
Have a seat.

07:41.619 --> 07:42.100
Alright.

07:47.140 --> 07:47.700
Uh...

07:48.820 --> 07:49.340
It's fine, really.

07:57.419 --> 07:58.299
I tune out

07:58.299 --> 07:59.900
everyone else's gossip,

08:00.299 --> 08:00.979
but not yours.

08:01.859 --> 08:03.059
You're my...

08:05.859 --> 08:06.539
most trusted senior.

08:08.580 --> 08:09.660
So you do remember I'm your senior.

08:10.100 --> 08:11.419
Couldn't even call me that earlier.

08:12.379 --> 08:12.939
My bad.

08:13.419 --> 08:15.059
This is my apology gift.

08:18.179 --> 08:19.780
I passed by the shop on the way,

08:20.220 --> 08:21.179
so I grabbed one for you.

08:21.939 --> 08:22.979
Wait, this is the milk tea shop

08:22.979 --> 08:23.939
from the university town!

08:24.340 --> 08:25.419
It's still open?

08:28.539 --> 08:29.020
Here.

08:29.340 --> 08:29.820
Thanks.

08:32.859 --> 08:33.820
Double bean milk tea,

08:34.299 --> 08:35.419
full sugar, no tea base.

08:35.979 --> 08:36.900
Swapped cow's milk for soy milk,

08:37.220 --> 08:38.700
red beans only, no mung beans.

08:42.379 --> 08:44.619
I still have the memo from

08:44.619 --> 08:45.379
when I ran errands for seniors

08:45.379 --> 08:46.180
back in the day,

08:46.499 --> 08:47.619
just without the names attached.

08:48.940 --> 08:49.820
Lucky I got it right, otherwise

08:50.300 --> 08:51.979
I'd be making things even worse.

08:53.180 --> 08:53.859
That's so thoughtful of you.

08:55.220 --> 08:56.100
I don't have much

08:56.100 --> 08:56.859
to offer here,

08:57.619 --> 08:58.659
let me get you a glass of warm water.

08:59.739 --> 09:00.899
Sure, warm water is perfect.

09:01.379 --> 09:02.700
I'm resting my voice these days,

09:02.779 --> 09:03.340
so I'm laying off sugary drinks.

09:03.379 --> 09:04.739
Alright, one second.

09:14.060 --> 09:14.420
Here you go.

09:15.659 --> 09:16.060
Thanks.

09:21.739 --> 09:22.499
Oh, by the way,

09:23.100 --> 09:24.659
is that your car downstairs?

09:26.899 --> 09:27.540
Yeah, that's mine.

09:28.060 --> 09:28.820
It's a mess.

09:29.060 --> 09:29.979
It rained on my drive

09:29.979 --> 09:30.659
from Su City,

09:30.820 --> 09:32.180
got all splashed with mud.

09:34.659 --> 09:36.259
You came all the way from Su City?

09:37.100 --> 09:37.940
You could've just told me

09:37.940 --> 09:39.340
you were doing that for the game.

09:39.820 --> 09:41.060
It's definitely not for the game.

09:41.859 --> 09:42.859
I wanted to see you anyway,

09:43.180 --> 09:44.139
the livestream just gave me

09:44.139 --> 09:45.019
an excuse to call.

09:50.340 --> 09:51.180
There's something

09:51.580 --> 09:52.820
I need to apologize for in person,

09:53.100 --> 09:53.859
I couldn't live with myself if I didn't.

09:57.100 --> 09:58.420
Give me one second,

09:58.580 --> 09:59.499
I need to take care of something.

10:00.019 --> 10:00.460
Sure.

10:15.979 --> 10:16.619
Mr. Xu,

10:16.619 --> 10:17.580
I'm so sorry.

10:17.979 --> 10:19.100
My phone died just now,

10:19.100 --> 10:19.779
so I couldn't

10:19.779 --> 10:20.499
check in with you.

10:21.300 --> 10:21.859
Sorry.

10:24.619 --> 10:25.700
A friend just came over.

10:32.220 --> 10:34.019
You weren't looking at Li Shican.

10:34.659 --> 10:36.220
You just saw him

10:36.220 --> 10:37.739
and got reminded of that Xu guy again.

10:39.659 --> 10:42.259
Mr. Xu?

10:45.100 --> 10:45.700
Hello.

10:47.019 --> 10:47.700
Sorry about that.

10:49.700 --> 10:50.739
Don't check in with me.

10:51.580 --> 10:52.779
Check in with the police instead.

10:54.180 --> 10:54.739
Police?

10:57.180 --> 10:58.779
He's your retained attorney?

11:00.139 --> 11:00.540
Yeah.

11:12.220 --> 11:12.820
I need to take this.

11:15.979 --> 11:16.420
Hello?

11:16.940 --> 11:17.420
[Shican,]

11:17.659 --> 11:18.820
[the cops just arrested me downstairs!]

11:19.100 --> 11:19.779
[Come help me!]

11:28.700 --> 11:29.499
Just a moment, you two.

11:29.979 --> 11:30.460
Thanks.

11:34.300 --> 11:36.019
Let's wait over there.

11:40.499 --> 11:41.820
I'm so sorry.

11:42.340 --> 11:43.220
I overreacted,

11:43.659 --> 11:45.180
and got you and your friend

11:45.180 --> 11:46.060
dragged into this investigation.

11:46.300 --> 11:46.979
My bad.

11:48.060 --> 11:49.259
I should be the one apologizing.

11:49.499 --> 11:50.700
I didn't handle things properly

11:50.700 --> 11:51.820
with Cen Sisi.

12:00.779 --> 12:02.139
She told me

12:02.940 --> 12:03.899
you two were childhood friends?

12:04.899 --> 12:05.979
I'm from Su City,

12:06.139 --> 12:07.019
she's from Hang City.

12:07.499 --> 12:08.340
How could we be childhood friends?

12:09.659 --> 12:10.460
Her dad moved to Su City

12:10.460 --> 12:11.499
for business back then,

12:11.619 --> 12:13.100
so she transferred schools here.

12:13.499 --> 12:14.979
We were classmates for two years,

12:15.180 --> 12:16.460
then went to the same college.

12:17.060 --> 12:18.499
I guess that's why

12:18.499 --> 12:19.859
she thinks we're practically

12:20.940 --> 12:21.700
childhood friends.

12:24.659 --> 12:25.659
She's had

12:25.659 --> 12:28.940
a crush on me for years.

12:30.100 --> 12:31.300
I have a private Weibo account

12:31.580 --> 12:33.420
that follows your Lily Vale account,

12:33.739 --> 12:35.700
she tracked you down through that,

12:35.940 --> 12:38.619
and probably got the wrong idea.

12:45.499 --> 12:46.979
So how did you know I'm Lily Vale?

12:49.340 --> 12:50.300
You asked me

12:50.300 --> 12:51.340
to fix your computer back in college,

12:51.460 --> 12:51.979
remember?

12:52.700 --> 12:53.700
I saw your pen name

12:53.700 --> 12:55.420
on a file name,

12:55.499 --> 12:57.180
remembered it,

12:57.180 --> 12:58.340
and started following you.

13:01.499 --> 13:04.259
You've been hiding it well.

13:06.139 --> 13:08.100
I figured you creators

13:08.100 --> 13:09.580
like to keep your online

13:09.580 --> 13:10.979
and real lives separate,

13:11.300 --> 13:12.739
otherwise it's like

13:12.739 --> 13:13.340
baring it all online.

13:14.700 --> 13:15.340
But don't worry,

13:15.700 --> 13:17.180
I don't stalk your account.

13:17.659 --> 13:19.060
That's why I only found out about this

13:19.060 --> 13:19.979
after I came back to China.

13:20.259 --> 13:21.220
If I'd known earlier,

13:21.379 --> 13:22.060
I would've handled it right away.

13:25.180 --> 13:26.899
Someone's been deleting comments,

13:27.100 --> 13:27.859
and leaking Cen Sisi's

13:27.859 --> 13:28.979
personal info.

13:29.659 --> 13:31.019
Was that your PR team?

13:32.499 --> 13:33.940
I told them to moderate the comments.

13:34.259 --> 13:36.259
I had no idea

13:36.779 --> 13:37.619
about the info leak.

13:39.220 --> 13:41.899
Could it have been done by netizens?

13:44.340 --> 13:45.139
Really?

13:47.379 --> 13:49.100
Either way, I got you into this mess,

13:49.100 --> 13:50.379
and I'll clean it up.

13:50.779 --> 13:52.139
The hype's died down now.

13:52.340 --> 13:53.739
Just focus on your lawsuit,

13:54.060 --> 13:56.139
leave the rest to me.

13:57.420 --> 13:58.019
No need.

13:58.540 --> 13:59.859
This isn't your fault anyway,

14:00.300 --> 14:01.859
and you're swamped right now.

14:02.300 --> 14:03.340
Don't waste your time on this.

14:03.820 --> 14:05.420
I have a lawyer handling it for me.

14:09.659 --> 14:10.100
Oh, by the way,

14:10.420 --> 14:11.700
I saw your

14:12.019 --> 14:13.700
lawyer's letter was signed

14:13.700 --> 14:14.460
by Zhikun Law Firm.

14:15.060 --> 14:15.979
Is Mr. Xu

14:17.259 --> 14:19.019
with Zhikun?

14:19.619 --> 14:20.180
Yeah.

14:20.619 --> 14:22.940
Is he reliable?

14:24.659 --> 14:25.180
Don't worry,

14:25.460 --> 14:26.300
he's extremely professional

14:26.460 --> 14:27.139
and experienced.

14:53.019 --> 14:53.979
Finally found you,

14:55.659 --> 14:56.300
Xu.

14:58.340 --> 15:00.940
Looks like you've found her too.

16:18.060 --> 16:18.940
Did you find

16:20.499 --> 16:21.659
your Hanazawa Rui?

16:41.460 --> 16:42.220
[Mr. Xu,]

16:42.460 --> 16:43.859
[I'm so sorry about today.]

16:44.100 --> 16:45.060
[I made you worry for nothing.]

17:03.499 --> 17:04.300
[Mr. Xu,]

17:05.060 --> 17:06.180
[have you read the document?]

17:12.179 --> 17:13.780
He hasn't replied to a single one.

17:18.139 --> 17:18.899
Well, fair enough.

17:20.459 --> 17:22.060
Anyone would be upset

17:22.060 --> 17:22.859
after being messed around like that,

17:23.060 --> 17:23.980
especially when the police got called.

17:28.179 --> 17:28.820
Plus,

17:29.740 --> 17:31.179
he's super busy to begin with.

17:34.379 --> 17:34.939
Or maybe

17:34.939 --> 17:36.219
he just hasn't seen them?

17:46.500 --> 17:47.219
[Mr. Xu,]

17:47.580 --> 17:49.379
[have you been busy these past two days?]

17:49.899 --> 17:50.859
[When will you have time]

17:50.859 --> 17:52.379
[to go over the case with me?]

18:05.419 --> 18:06.139
[In ten minutes.]

18:09.939 --> 18:10.899
[I'll go turn on my computer.]

18:12.980 --> 18:13.500
[No need.]

18:13.540 --> 18:14.340
[I'll be downstairs]

18:14.740 --> 18:15.500
[at your place in ten minutes.]

18:39.020 --> 18:39.780
No need to rush.

18:40.540 --> 18:41.459
Sorry to keep you waiting,

18:41.459 --> 18:42.340
Mr. Xu.

18:43.300 --> 18:44.540
[All because of a silly mix-up,]

18:44.820 --> 18:45.780
[the great Mr. Xu]

18:45.780 --> 18:46.699
[didn't reply to a single word from me]

18:46.699 --> 18:47.659
[for two days.]

18:48.260 --> 18:50.020
[How dare I keep a big shot like you]

18:50.020 --> 18:51.219
[waiting even a second longer?]

18:53.139 --> 18:54.939
Get in. We're going to the firm.

19:13.580 --> 19:14.419
Well,

19:14.980 --> 19:16.340
what are you doing near my place?

19:17.740 --> 19:19.740
On the way from the airport to the firm.

19:20.540 --> 19:23.459
[On the way from the airport to the firm?]

19:27.820 --> 19:28.619
Thanks for picking me up.

19:37.379 --> 19:37.820
Hello?

19:38.699 --> 19:39.219
Ms. Zhang?

19:41.459 --> 19:42.379
Got it, I understand.

19:43.859 --> 19:44.300
Mr. Xu,

19:44.899 --> 19:46.379
Ms. Zhang ran into an emergency

19:46.379 --> 19:47.500
on a case at the construction site,

19:47.500 --> 19:48.580
I have to head over there.

19:50.020 --> 19:50.859
Then drop my luggage off

19:50.859 --> 19:51.980
at my apartment once you're done.

19:52.659 --> 19:53.060
Sure.

20:37.740 --> 20:38.980
Should I get a taxi?

20:57.500 --> 20:58.740
Or we can talk at my place?

20:59.459 --> 21:00.820
We can do it another time.

21:00.899 --> 21:01.740
I'll head back to the office first.

21:02.020 --> 21:03.459
No, it's totally fine. This way please.

21:12.379 --> 21:13.100
Watch the steps.

21:21.859 --> 21:23.740
[He's only mad at you for two days,]

21:24.459 --> 21:26.020
[and look at you groveling like this.]

21:37.139 --> 21:37.899
[Oh shoot.]

21:39.459 --> 21:40.020
What's wrong?

21:42.020 --> 21:43.020
Nothing.

21:44.100 --> 21:45.139
Just a moment.

22:13.619 --> 22:14.500
Come on in.

22:28.619 --> 22:29.179
Sorry,

22:29.619 --> 22:30.859
I don't have men's slippers here.

22:31.419 --> 22:32.659
Just keep your shoes on.

22:49.699 --> 22:50.540
That's where I sat

22:50.540 --> 22:51.699
for my videos earlier.

22:56.219 --> 22:57.340
A friend was over just now.

23:06.740 --> 23:07.419
Can I

23:07.619 --> 23:08.580
get you something to drink?

23:09.459 --> 23:10.219
Coffee's fine.

23:10.780 --> 23:11.659
Is instant okay?

23:13.780 --> 23:15.459
Alright, have a seat.

23:39.699 --> 23:40.580
[I was so focused on]

23:40.580 --> 23:41.820
[not wasting his trip,]

23:42.260 --> 23:43.020
[I forgot about the jet lag.]

23:43.899 --> 23:45.139
[I should've told him to go home.]

25:43.260 --> 25:43.780
Mr. Xu...

27:08.419 --> 27:09.179
Sorry,

27:09.619 --> 27:10.179
I fell asleep.

27:15.820 --> 27:16.300
Hello?

27:18.780 --> 27:19.459
I just fell asleep.

27:21.619 --> 27:22.139
Haven't eaten yet.

27:24.260 --> 27:24.699
Bye.

27:31.179 --> 27:32.939
You haven't eaten?

27:35.899 --> 27:37.540
Do you want to go get something first?

27:43.780 --> 27:44.379
It's too hot out.

27:48.419 --> 27:49.540
Then should I order takeout?

27:52.300 --> 27:53.179
You don't eat takeout.

27:59.139 --> 28:01.659
How about I make you something?

28:02.939 --> 28:03.899
I have food at home,

28:04.219 --> 28:06.459
we can make do with what we have.

28:10.139 --> 28:10.899
If it's not too much trouble.

28:12.340 --> 28:12.939
It's no trouble at all.

28:13.379 --> 28:14.340
Come to the kitchen,

28:14.340 --> 28:15.300
see if there's anything you want.

28:22.100 --> 28:23.219
With the ingredients we have,

28:23.219 --> 28:25.100
I can make sandwiches or pasta.

28:25.500 --> 28:26.540
Whatever you prefer.

28:30.060 --> 28:30.580
This one.

28:33.659 --> 28:34.260
Your stomach

28:34.300 --> 28:35.580
hasn't fully adapted to Western food yet.

28:38.820 --> 28:39.659
How do you want it cooked?

28:40.300 --> 28:40.820
Fried.

28:42.179 --> 28:43.179
Go sit in the living room for a bit.

28:53.300 --> 28:55.980
[These aren't really good for frying.]

28:57.500 --> 28:58.699
[He probably wants]

28:58.699 --> 29:00.020
[Su-style lard rice cakes.]

29:17.699 --> 29:18.300
You know,

29:18.859 --> 29:19.540
I swapped it

29:19.540 --> 29:20.699
for Su-style lard rice cakes.

29:21.020 --> 29:21.740
You probably

29:21.980 --> 29:23.020
don't get to eat these often abroad.

29:24.540 --> 29:24.939
Thanks.

29:35.580 --> 29:36.419
How did you know

29:36.899 --> 29:37.699
I'm from Su City?

29:42.379 --> 29:43.340
I looked it up.

29:43.820 --> 29:45.179
There are news articles about you.

29:48.699 --> 29:49.859
Why did you look into me?

29:54.020 --> 29:54.859
Just

29:55.540 --> 29:56.580
basic background

29:56.580 --> 29:57.419
on my attorney.

29:58.300 --> 29:58.939
I also know

29:58.939 --> 30:00.659
Mr. Liu is from Hang City.

30:06.699 --> 30:07.219
Eat up

30:07.899 --> 30:08.859
while it's hot.

30:09.699 --> 30:10.139
Alright.

30:23.619 --> 30:24.859
[He's eating so politely.]

30:25.179 --> 30:26.740
[Does he like it or not?]

30:38.580 --> 30:39.219
Want some?

30:40.500 --> 30:41.260
I'm good.

30:42.179 --> 30:43.260
You eat up,

30:44.100 --> 30:44.899
I'll go wash the dishes.

31:09.379 --> 31:10.500
[Well, his appetite sure isn't polite.]

31:11.060 --> 31:12.699
[The frying turned out great today.]

31:14.580 --> 31:15.179
Are you full,

31:15.419 --> 31:16.100
Mr. Xu?

31:22.740 --> 31:23.340
I haven't read it yet.

31:25.459 --> 31:27.060
Have you been busy these days?

31:29.980 --> 31:30.740
Haven't checked WeChat either.

31:36.820 --> 31:38.340
[So he wasn't ignoring me on purpose.]

31:38.699 --> 31:39.540
[I knew it.]

31:39.540 --> 31:40.939
[He wouldn't be that petty.]

31:59.419 --> 32:00.659
Hello? What's up?

32:06.340 --> 32:07.300
The cat food is in the

32:07.300 --> 32:08.980
lower cabinet in the kitchen.

32:10.300 --> 32:10.740
Yeah.

32:15.020 --> 32:15.859
Just do whatever you think is best.

32:18.619 --> 32:20.459
First off, he has a cat.

32:20.659 --> 32:21.740
Second, he doesn't bathe

32:21.740 --> 32:22.699
the cat himself.

32:22.699 --> 32:23.980
So

32:23.980 --> 32:24.459
who does?

32:26.859 --> 32:27.619
Are you saying

32:29.020 --> 32:30.419
there's someone else at his place?

32:32.260 --> 32:33.260
He has a girlfriend?

32:35.500 --> 32:36.379
He could just

32:36.379 --> 32:37.899
take the cat to a pet groomer,

32:37.899 --> 32:39.219
but what you're saying

32:39.219 --> 32:40.139
is definitely possible too.

32:47.659 --> 32:48.139
Ruan Yu,

32:50.020 --> 32:50.980
I need to sleep for a bit.

33:02.659 --> 33:03.379
What,

33:05.219 --> 33:06.459
you're sleeping here?

33:07.699 --> 33:08.340
How about...

33:12.179 --> 33:12.780
Hey...

33:22.379 --> 33:24.179
He fell asleep that fast.

33:40.859 --> 33:42.540
Being a lawyer

33:42.540 --> 33:44.020
really is such an exhausting job.

35:50.940 --> 35:51.819
Mr. Xu,

35:52.659 --> 35:55.420
you've barely been in the office lately.

35:55.980 --> 35:57.900
It's been half a month

35:57.900 --> 35:59.139
since we last saw each other, right?

36:01.699 --> 36:02.900
Want a tea egg? My treat.

36:03.219 --> 36:03.699
No, thanks.

36:04.179 --> 36:05.219
I overate last night,

36:05.219 --> 36:06.179
still haven't digested it yet.

36:06.460 --> 36:07.139
What did you eat

36:07.299 --> 36:08.380
that's still sitting with you this long?

36:09.100 --> 36:10.179
Fried lard rice cakes.

36:12.420 --> 36:13.699
How fancy of you.

36:13.699 --> 36:15.940
Naturally, it's a Su City specialty.

36:17.179 --> 36:18.860
Making fried rice cakes for yourself?

36:18.860 --> 36:19.580
Nice.

36:20.139 --> 36:21.420
Actually, I didn't make them.

36:29.420 --> 36:30.219
What's the story?

36:31.779 --> 36:32.699
Ruan Yu made them for me.

36:33.420 --> 36:33.819
Who?

36:34.540 --> 36:35.100
Ruan Yu.

36:35.580 --> 36:35.980
Why would she

36:35.980 --> 36:36.779
make you fried rice cakes?

36:36.779 --> 36:37.500
What's going on between you two?

36:39.500 --> 36:40.860
Is it weird for a client to make

36:40.860 --> 36:42.540
fried rice cakes for their attorney?

36:42.779 --> 36:43.460
Are you kidding?

36:43.460 --> 36:44.420
What client? What attorney?

36:44.420 --> 36:44.860
Since when do clients make

36:44.860 --> 36:45.779
fried rice cakes for their lawyers?

36:46.299 --> 36:47.900
Depends on the client,

36:48.100 --> 36:49.100
and the attorney.

36:49.100 --> 36:49.699
How so?

36:50.380 --> 36:51.339
Well, it can't be an attorney

36:51.339 --> 36:52.460
who's getting ahead of himself.

36:54.580 --> 36:57.179
Being likable is a gift, after all.

37:04.860 --> 37:05.619
Now grab your bag.

37:05.739 --> 37:06.259
It's time for work.

37:07.619 --> 37:08.699
Did you just insult me?

37:09.380 --> 37:10.500
I swear you did, but I have no proof.

37:31.299 --> 37:32.540
[When are you gonna update?]

37:33.219 --> 37:34.420
[My comfort read,]

37:34.699 --> 37:35.900
[please come back soon.]

37:38.580 --> 37:40.339
What writer doesn't get writer's block?

37:41.500 --> 37:42.580
This time's different.

37:43.619 --> 37:45.540
The male lead's based on someone I know.

37:46.139 --> 37:46.779
How am I supposed

37:46.779 --> 37:48.219
to keep writing like nothing's wrong?

37:50.860 --> 37:52.420
[I'm convinced the author's innocent now.]

37:52.980 --> 37:55.100
[Just curious, is this book]

37:55.100 --> 37:56.739
[really based on her real life?]

37:56.940 --> 37:58.020
[Same here.]

37:58.500 --> 37:59.339
[This whole thing blew up so bad.]

37:59.619 --> 38:00.580
[Does the real-life male lead]

38:00.580 --> 38:01.100
[even know about it?]

38:12.420 --> 38:14.179
Anyone still working at this hour

38:14.739 --> 38:16.460
must be the elite of this city.

38:20.460 --> 38:21.179
[Mr. Xu,]

38:21.380 --> 38:22.179
[I got your email.]

38:22.619 --> 38:24.060
[Thank you for working]

38:24.420 --> 38:25.020
[on my case so late.]

38:26.380 --> 38:27.100
[Just killing time]

38:27.179 --> 38:27.619
[while I get over my jet lag.]

38:31.100 --> 38:32.020
[If you're still up,]

38:32.299 --> 38:33.380
[we can go over the case.]

38:34.659 --> 38:35.779
[Sure. Video call?]

38:36.460 --> 38:36.940
[Voice call is fine.]

38:55.619 --> 38:56.299
Sorry,

38:56.699 --> 38:57.860
hold on one second.

38:58.060 --> 38:59.060
I need to go grab a document downstairs.

39:00.380 --> 39:00.900
Alright.

39:11.139 --> 39:12.060
Mr. Xu?

39:13.420 --> 39:14.060
I'm here.

39:17.179 --> 39:17.779
Well,

39:18.580 --> 39:20.580
is it raining where you are?

39:23.060 --> 39:23.699
It's pouring right now.

39:24.179 --> 39:24.980
Guess we're

39:25.500 --> 39:26.860
under the same rain cloud then.

39:42.900 --> 39:43.860
I'm back.

39:44.739 --> 39:45.219
Alright.

39:46.580 --> 39:47.420
Let's

39:48.339 --> 39:49.819
start with the third section.

39:51.380 --> 39:52.179
This part is about

39:53.860 --> 39:56.460
the female lead, who's scared of thunder,

39:57.420 --> 39:58.900
caught in an art museum by heavy rain.

39:59.900 --> 40:02.139
She overhears the male lead playing piano,

40:02.860 --> 40:04.219
and it calms her down.

40:05.739 --> 40:06.940
[This isn't in]

40:06.940 --> 40:07.460
[the other novel at all.]

40:08.179 --> 40:09.580
Do we need to bring this up?

40:10.420 --> 40:11.779
The descriptions of

40:11.980 --> 40:13.060
the piano room in both novels

40:13.060 --> 40:14.299
are actually quite similar.

40:15.060 --> 40:15.900
All piano rooms

40:15.900 --> 40:16.739
look pretty much the same.

40:17.219 --> 40:18.100
Did you forget?

40:20.819 --> 40:21.460
Forget what?

40:28.100 --> 40:29.259
Did you forget

40:29.259 --> 40:30.619
to switch to WiFi?

40:31.139 --> 40:32.420
[Your connection seems bad,]

40:32.420 --> 40:33.619
[I can barely hear you.]

40:40.420 --> 40:41.219
I already switched.

40:43.779 --> 40:44.420
It's good now,

40:44.659 --> 40:45.420
I can hear you clearly.

40:45.940 --> 40:47.460
Alright, let's keep going.

40:49.219 --> 40:50.179
In the next section,

40:50.980 --> 40:52.860
the female lead publicly turns down

40:52.860 --> 40:54.100
a male classmate who's been

40:54.100 --> 40:54.699
harassing her,

40:55.139 --> 40:55.819
telling him to stop

40:55.819 --> 40:57.139
disturbing her studies.

40:57.860 --> 40:58.940
The male lead

40:58.940 --> 41:00.020
sees this,

41:00.179 --> 41:01.659
and he won't disrupt her studies either.

41:01.860 --> 41:02.540
So he never confesses

41:02.540 --> 41:03.819
his feelings to her.

41:04.699 --> 41:06.980
Right, I checked, The Poet

41:06.980 --> 41:07.900
hasn't written about

41:07.900 --> 41:08.580
why the male lead

41:08.580 --> 41:09.819
never confessed yet.

41:10.460 --> 41:12.139
This part won't be called a trope copy?

41:12.619 --> 41:13.699
But this trope

41:14.060 --> 41:15.060
is a bit unreasonable.

41:17.259 --> 41:18.659
[Is my writing that unreasonable?]

41:20.339 --> 41:22.020
But the biggest worry for high schoolers

41:22.540 --> 41:23.460
is their studies.

41:24.659 --> 41:25.500
What other reason

41:26.299 --> 41:27.339
would the male lead have

41:27.339 --> 41:27.940
for not confessing?

41:31.460 --> 41:32.819
Not every high schooler

41:33.860 --> 41:34.819
is that lucky.

41:39.060 --> 41:41.460
I was being too absolute.

41:47.259 --> 41:48.659
Will this trope

41:49.460 --> 41:50.900
affect the lawsuit?

41:53.540 --> 41:54.219
It's fine,

41:54.540 --> 41:55.580
I'm just giving you a heads-up.

41:56.580 --> 41:57.299
You still need

41:57.460 --> 41:58.980
to keep updating your novel,

41:59.580 --> 42:00.980
so if you sort out your train of thought

42:01.179 --> 42:01.900
and resume updates soon,

42:02.420 --> 42:02.940
it'll help turn the public opinion

42:02.940 --> 42:04.339
around for the better.

42:06.420 --> 42:07.100
Yeah.

42:23.860 --> 42:24.460
The rain stopped.

42:45.500 --> 42:46.619
It's pouring so hard.

42:47.219 --> 42:47.860
I should've never come

42:47.860 --> 42:48.900
to feed the cats today.

43:11.380 --> 43:12.219
[Is that him?]

44:02.580 --> 44:03.259
[Xu Huaisong,]

44:04.179 --> 44:05.020
[your bright,]

44:05.020 --> 44:06.420
[untainted boyish charm]

44:07.219 --> 44:08.739
[cleared up every single]

44:09.299 --> 44:09.940
[rainy season]

44:11.020 --> 44:12.179
[of my youth.]

44:56.980 --> 44:57.659
Hello? Dad.

44:58.980 --> 45:00.179
Alright, I'm coming out now.

45:11.139 --> 45:13.580
The rain stopped here too.

45:14.940 --> 45:15.819
Let's keep going then.

45:18.060 --> 45:18.540
Alright.

46:06.060 --> 46:06.540
Ruan Yu?

46:46.339 --> 46:46.860
What's wrong?

46:47.860 --> 46:49.219
I'm so sorry,

46:49.900 --> 46:50.699
I accidentally fell asleep

46:50.699 --> 46:51.580
last night.

46:53.339 --> 46:54.619
Why didn't you hang up?

46:55.659 --> 46:57.819
I must've fallen asleep too around then.

47:02.980 --> 47:03.380
Alright,

47:05.819 --> 47:06.940
I'll hang up then.

47:12.139 --> 47:13.380
What's that noise?

47:14.619 --> 47:15.299
An ambulance.

47:17.779 --> 47:18.179
Why is there

47:18.179 --> 47:19.299
an ambulance siren?

47:20.100 --> 47:21.540
I'm at the hospital.
